Sonarr is a PVR for Usenet and BitTorrent users. It can monitor
multiple RSS feeds for new episodes of your favorite shows and will
grab, sort and rename them. It can also be configured to
automatically upgrade the quality of files already downloaded when
a better quality format becomes available.

Sonarr should not be run as root. By default the user is 'sonarr'
and the group is 'sonarr.' You can create this user and group like this: 

  # useradd -r -c "Sonarr User" -m /var/lib/sonarr -g sonarr sonarr

If you don't want to use the defualts, you can change the default user and group:

  # USER=youruser GROUP=yourgroup ./sonarr.SlackBuild

To run at start-up make sure your init script is executable:

  # chmod +x /etc/rc.d/rc.sonarr
